STATE OF CONNECTICUT v. PRINCE ALEXANDER (SC 15622)

Callahan, C. J., and Katz, Palmer, McDonald and Peters, Js.

Argued June 5 officially released July 15, 1997 *692Michael A. Fusco and Yvonne M. Schoff, certified legal interns, with whom was Richard Emanuel, assistant public defender, for the appellant (defendant). Timothy J. Sugrue, executive assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Michael Dearington, state’s attorney, and Christopher Alexy, assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state).

Opinion

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
